-{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-25T20:08:30.296Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777147710296_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-003 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-003_20260425T183959Z_1777147676.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-25\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py`\n- `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` matches the requirements:\n- It issues `/b_alloc` and `/b_allocRead` via `BufferLoader` if the buffer is not yet loaded (`record.buffer_id is None`).\n- It issues `/s_new sw_sampler` with the correct arguments, including node ID, buffer number, and synthesis parameters (amp, grain size, density, position, etc.).\n- It returns a `SamplerHandle` whose `release()` method correctly emits `/n_set <node_id> gate 0`.\n- It correlates `record.gain_db` into the linear `amp` value using the formula `amp * 10**(gain_db/20)`.\n- It applies per-mode effects presets by sending `/n_set` to the `fx_node_id` before the `/s_new` message.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete and covers all acceptance criteria:\n- `SamplerDispatcher` handles buffer acquisition and synth spawning.\n- `SamplerHandle` provides the required release path.\n- Per-mode effects presets for `working_ambience` and `evening_reflection` are implemented as a seed table.\n- Gain correlation is correctly applied.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows established patterns in the `senseweave` toolset. It correctly interfaces with `BufferLoader` and uses `Protocol` for dependencies like `OSCSender` and `SampleRecord` to maintain loose coupling.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities or leaked secrets were identified. The implementation uses standard OSC messaging for local `scsynth` communication.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured and documented. The tests in `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` are comprehensive, using a mock OSC client to verify message ordering and content.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The seed `FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE` table is correctly positioned for future expansion in T-020.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-003@20260425t183959z-verify.md"}}
